Consider the set $\Delta=$\HOLtm{{{w | w IN M.frame.world /\ !phi.phi IN s ==> satis M w phi\}| FINITE s /\ s â Î£\} âª {Y | (only_see M Y) IN w /\ Y â M.frame.world\}}. Similar as in the proof of \texttt{prop_2_59_i}, we check $\Delta$ has the finite intersection property. The only nontrivial thing to check is that for $a$ in the first set of union and $b$ in the second set of union, we have $a\cap b\ne\emptyset$.

